# Linux Cheat-sheet (Kali & general)

## System & user
- Show IP: `ip a`
- Hostname: `hostname`
- Current user: `whoami`
- Switch user: `sudo -i`
- List processes: `ps aux | less`
- Kill process: `kill <pid>` / `kill -9 <pid>`

## Files & directories
- List files: `ls`
- Change dir: `cd /path/to/dir`
- Copy / move / remove: `cp`, `mv`, `rm -rf`
- Show file content: `cat file`, `less file`, `head -n 50 file`
- Edit files: `nano file`

## Permissions
- Show perms: `ls -l`
- Change perms: `chmod 755 file`
- Change owner: `chown user:group file`

## Networking
- Resolve DNS: `dig example.com` or `nslookup example.com`
- Test connectivity: `ping -c 4 <ip>`
- TCP/UDP scan (nmap): `nmap -sC -sV -oN out.txt <target>`
- List open ports (local): `ss -tuln` or `netstat -tnlp`

## Package management (Debian)
- Update: `sudo apt update`
- Upgrade: `sudo apt upgrade -y`
- Install: `sudo apt install -y <pkg>`

## Useful tools
- curl: `curl -v http://<ip>/`
- wget: `wget http://<ip>/file`
- ssh: `ssh user@host`
- grep: `grep -i 'pattern' file`
- find: `find / -name '*.conf' 2>/dev/null | less`

## Quick file transfer (between host & VM)
- From host to VM (if SSH available): `scp file user@<vm_ip>:/tmp/`
